    {
      "text": "\n                        \n\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t",
      "url": "https://thephiladelphiacitizen.org/july-4-speeches/"
    },
    {
      "text": "\n\t\t\t\t\t\tThe Fourth of July Thoughts We Need to Read Now\t\t\t\t\t\t\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\tJuly 4th means different things to different Americans. Here, a host of Independence Day perspectives \u2014 from Frederick Douglass, Susan B. Anthony, Ronald Reagan and more \u2014 that remind us what it means to be free\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\tBy Roxanne Patel Shepelavy\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\n\t\t\t\t\t",
      "url": "https://thephiladelphiacitizen.org/july-4-speeches/"
    },
    {
      "text": "\n\t\n\t\t\n\t\tListen: This Fourth, \u201cRemember the Ladies\u201d\t\tCitizen Board Member and MSNBC host Ali Velshi invokes a letter by Abigail Adams to her husband, John, imploring him to remember women's rights when forming this country.\n\t\t\tBy Ali Velshi\t\n\t",
      "url": "https://thephiladelphiacitizen.org/listen-this-fourth-remember-the-ladies/"
    },
    {
      "text": "\n\t\n\t\t\n\t\tFun Things to Do in Philly For the 4th of July\t\tWhere to see 4th of July fireworks, a massive Independence Day party on the Parkway, concerts, parades, free museum days and more\n\t\t\tBy Josh Middleton\t\n\t",
      "url": "https://thephiladelphiacitizen.org/things-to-do-philly-weekend/"
    },
    {
      "text": "\n\t\n\t\t\n\t\tThe Rookie\u2019s Guide to Biking in Philly\t\tExpert tips for hitting Philadelphia's mean streets on two wheels \n\t\t\tBy Jessica Blatt Press\t\n\t",
      "url": "https://thephiladelphiacitizen.org/biking-philadelphia-guide/"
    },
    {
      "text": "\n\t\n\t\t\n\t\tSussing Out \u2014 and Stopping \u2014 Illegal Dumping\t\tPhilly has more illegal dumping surveillance cameras than other major cities, but far fewer arrests and convictions. Here\u2019s what we know about illegal dumpers \u2014 and a system that rarely stops them.\n\t\t\tBy Nick Russo\t\n\t",
      "url": "https://thephiladelphiacitizen.org/surveillance-cameras-illegal-dumping-philly/"
    },
    {
      "text": "\n\t\n\t\t\n\t\tWatch: Citizen Book Club with Dan Pfeiffer\t\tThe author, podcaster and political insider spoke to a Philadelphia Citizen audience about uniting America by telling the truth.\n\t\t\tBy Lauren McCutcheon\t\n\t",
      "url": "https://thephiladelphiacitizen.org/dan-pfeiffer-philly/"
    },
    {
      "text": "\n\t\n\t\t\n\t\tThe Spectacular Philly Hip-Hop Artist You Never Heard of\t\tLogan-born poet / musician Khemist is one of the most gifted artists Philly has produced this century. We just don\u2019t know it yet.\n\t\t\tBy James Peterson\t\n\t",
      "url": "https://thephiladelphiacitizen.org/khemist-hip-hop/"
    },
    {
      "text": "\n\t\n\t\t\n\t\tArt for Change: The Sound Sculptor\t\tNext in a series with Forman Arts Initiative, Philadelphia artist Ra\u00fal Romero merges sculpture with an invisible medium: sound\n\t\t\tBy Morgan Nitz\t\n\t",
      "url": "https://thephiladelphiacitizen.org/raul-romero-sound-sculptor/"
    },
    {
      "text": "\n\t\n\t\t\n\t\tWill the Supreme Court Bombshells Change How PA Votes?\t\tWhy are Josh Shapiro and Doug Mastriano neck and neck? Is Dr. Oz underwater? Is PA going red? Catching up with legendary political consultant Neil Oxman to understand the polling.\n\t\t\tBy Larry Platt\t\n\t",
      "url": "https://thephiladelphiacitizen.org/supreme-court-bombshells-pa/"
